DESIGN (vs round-4 base, attacking the binding constraint = 16x16 tile inefficiency):
  BM query rows/CTA      16   ->  64   (N204 tile, restores GEMM efficiency)
  warps/CTA               1   ->   4   (full SM compute, 2x2 over 64-row tile)
  inner mma     wmma m16n16k16  ->  mma.sync.m16n8k16 (N204 large-tile, 8/warp/Kstep)
  loads     wmma.load.global ->  cp.async.bulk.tensor TMA SWIZZLE_128B
  pipeline           none   ->  double-buffered K/V (slot[k+1] DMA || mma[k])
  Q reuse   HBM/block   ->  TMA-loaded ONCE into smem (resident)

STATIC REVIEW (PASS):
  - pure ASCII (0 non-ascii bytes) -- driver-JIT ptxas requirement met
  - instruction histogram N=2048: 5 cp.async.bulk.tensor (TMA) / 64
    mma.sync.m16n8k16 / 32 ldmatrix / 2 mbarrier.try_wait / 1 st.global (final
    O only -- S NEVER to HBM, moat preserved) / 8 bar.sync / 2 ex2.approx
  - mma layout: QK^T = mma.row.col with B=K via ldmatrix.trans (gives K^T,
    matches N204 B handling); P.V = mma.row.col with B=V non-trans (contraction
    over keys along smem rows)
  - mbarrier double-buffer: per-slot parity = (kb>>1)&1; prologue arrives slot0,
    in-loop issue-next arrives the OTHER slot -> exactly one arrive per slot use
    (traced: no double-arrive, no parity race)
  - register hygiene: lane consts (r55/r71/r90/r91) set once, read-only;
    mma/scatter scratch (r74-97, r150-151) disjoint from softmax/finalize
    (r100-116); kb/parity are dedicated named regs surviving the full loop
  - smem 82752 B < 102400 B/SM (needs MaxDynamicSharedMemorySize opt-in;
    binds occupancy to ~1 CTA/SM -- a known tradeoff, see residual analysis)

