VERDICT: ORANGE -- INSUFFICIENT (pre-registered <=1.10 NOT hit) + closed-negative finding
  "N204 standalone-GEMM roofline toolkit does NOT transplant to fused flash-attention --
   the 64x64 tile that buys roofline GEMM performance COSTS attention occupancy
   because fused attention has fundamentally different smem residency (Q + K + V + V^T +
   S + P + O simultaneously), forcing 1 CTA/SM. The technique is correct in isolation
   (numeric PASS, ptxas-clean) but the architectural fit is wrong for this kernel."

PAPER: NOT eligible (ORANGE, re-confirmation of an already-CLOSED-NEGATIVE wall via a
       new failed-axis -- paper_gate forbids per project.tape paper_significance).

NEXT-ROUND WEDGE (terminal recommendation):
  BM=32 (or 16) + REGISTER-RESIDENT O (acc in regs, not smem) + selective TMA
  to restore >=4 CTAs/SM occupancy WITHOUT abandoning TMA loads. Smem budget then
  Q(4K)+K(2x4K)+V(2x4K)+Vt(2x4K)+S(4K)+P(2K)+mlc=~34K -> 2 CTAs/SM, doubling occupancy.
